94	12 steps – From idea to discovery – Home - Home	12-steps-from-idea-to-discovery-home-home		Science	CERN's research has led to groundbreaking discoveries, including the existence of the Higgs boson, a fundamental particle that explains how other particles acquire mass. The stakes are high, as the outcomes of CERN's research have far-reaching implications for our understanding of the universe and the laws of physics that govern it.	Deep within the Swiss countryside, CERN's sprawling complex hums with activity. The organization's research has been a driving force behind some of the most significant scientific breakthroughs of the past century. At its heart lies the Large Hadron Collider (LHC), a 27-kilometer-long underground ring that smashes particles together at nearly the speed of light. The resulting collisions have yielded a wealth of data, which scientists are still working to decipher.\n\nAs the LHC continues to operate, researchers are pushing the boundaries of what is thought possible. The organization's focus on particle physics research has led to a deeper understanding of the fundamental nature of matter. The existence of the Higgs boson, discovered in 2012, was a major milestone in this journey. However, there is still much to be learned, and CERN's researchers are driven by an insatiable curiosity about the universe and its secrets.\n\nThe implications of CERN's research extend far beyond the scientific community. A deeper understanding of the laws of physics has the potential to revolutionize fields such as medicine, technology, and energy. As scientists continue to probe the mysteries of the universe, they are also pushing the boundaries of human knowledge and understanding.\n\nThe stakes are high, and the scientific community is abuzz with excitement. CERN's research has the potential to rewrite the textbooks on the fundamental nature of matter, and the world is watching with bated breath. As the organization continues to push the boundaries of what is thought possible, one thing is certain: the outcomes of CERN's research will have far-reaching implications for our understanding of the universe and the laws of physics that govern it.\n\nCERN's research is a testament to human ingenuity and the power of scientific inquiry. As the organization continues to explore the mysteries of the universe, it is clear that the journey is just beginning. The discoveries that lie ahead will be groundbreaking, and the world will be forever changed by the insights gained from CERN's research.\n\nThe Large Hadron Collider, CERN's flagship research facility, is a marvel of modern engineering. Its sheer scale and complexity are a testament to the organization's commitment to scientific inquiry. As researchers continue to probe the mysteries of the universe, the LHC remains at the forefront of the quest for knowledge.\n\nCERN's research has the potential to revolutionize our understanding of the universe and the laws of physics that govern it. The organization's focus on particle physics research has led to a deeper understanding of the fundamental nature of matter, and the discoveries that lie ahead will be groundbreaking.	\N	\N	\N	https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1446776811953-b23d57bd21aa?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1600&q=85	CERN, the world's largest particle physics research center, has been pushing the boundaries of human understanding for decades, but its latest endeavors are poised to rewrite the textbooks on the fundamental nature of matter.	["CERN is a research center involved in particle physics research.", "The Large Hadron Collider (LHC), operated by CERN, has been instrumental in making these discoveries.", "CERN is located in Europe.", "CERN's research has implications for our understanding of the universe and the laws of physics."]	{"heading": "The Story", "body": "Deep within the Swiss countryside, CERN's sprawling complex hums with activity. The organization's research has been a driving force behind some of the most