oducers. It's a reminder that the Oscars are not just a celebration of the past year's films, but a reflection of the industry's values and priorities. And as the Academy looks to the future, it's clear that human creativity and talent will remain at the heart of the Oscars.\\n\\nThe decision to exclude AI performers from the Oscars has sparked a lively debate in the media, with some praising the Academy's commitment to traditional values and others criticizing the move as a form of artistic elitism. As the industry continues to grapple with the implications of AI-generated content, the Oscars will remain at the forefront of the conversation."}	\N	\N	[{"label": "Germany", "type": "country", "summary": "DW reports: New Oscars rules exclude AI performers, require scripts written by human", "source_names": ["DW"]}, {"label": "United States", "type": "country", "summary": "DW.com reports: New Oscars rules: No AI actors, human-written scripts only", "source_names": ["DW.com"]}]	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	10	2	2	2	2026-05-06 05:31:01.645834	2026-05-06 05:51:56.929487
171	Kevin Smith stand-up shows announced for San Diego Comic-...	kevin-smith-stand-up-shows-announced-for-san-diego		Entertainment	Kevin Smith, the director and actor behind cult classics like Clerks and Mallrats, is set to bring his stand-up comedy to San Diego Comic-Con. The event, which has become a mecca for fans of science fiction, fantasy, and comic books, is about to get a whole lot more interesting – but with great excitement comes great parking anxiety.	San Diego Comic-Con has long been a hub for fans of science fiction, fantasy, and comic books, but this year's event is shaping up to be one of the most exciting yet. With Kevin Smith set to bring his stand-up comedy to the stage, attendees can expect a unique blend of humor and pop culture. As a director and actor, Smith has built a loyal following with cult classics like Clerks and Mallrats, and his stand-up shows are always a hit.\n\nBut while fans are busy counting down the days until the convention, parking details have been announced – and they're causing headaches. Ace Parking, the company responsible for parking logistics, has revealed the details, but it's unclear how this will impact attendees. With thousands of fans descending on the city, parking is always a major concern, and this year is no exception.\n\nAs the event draws near, fans are taking to social media to share their excitement – and their parking woes. "I'm so stoked to see Kevin Smith at Comic-Con," tweeted one fan, "but I'm not sure how I'm going to get there without losing my mind over parking." With the convention just around the corner, it's clear that parking will be a major issue – but with Kevin Smith's stand-up shows on the horizon, it's worth the hassle.\n\nFor fans of science fiction and fantasy, San Diego Comic-Con is a once-a-year opportunity to connect with like-minded individuals and celebrate their shared passions. And with Kevin Smith set to take the stage, this year's event is shaping up to be one of the most memorable yet. But as the convention draws near, it's clear that parking will be a major challenge – and one that attendees will need to navigate carefully.\n\nAs the event approaches, fans are bracing themselves for the crowds and chaos that come with Comic-Con. But with Kevin Smith's stand-up shows on the horizon, it's clear that this year's event will be one to remember. Whether you're a die-hard fan or just looking for a unique experience, San Diego Comic-Con is an event not to be missed – and with Kevin Smith on the bill, it's shaping up to be a wild ride.	\N	\N	\N	https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1598899134739-24c46f58b8c0?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1600&q=85	Kevin Smith's stand-up shows are coming to San Diego Comic-Con, but parking details are already causing headaches.	["Kevin Smith stand-up shows announced for San Diego Comic-Con**: The comedian and filmmaker will take the stage at the convention, which is scheduled to take place.", "What changed: Parking details have been announced, but the focus is on Kevin Smith's stand-up shows.", "Who is involved: Kevin Smith, San Diego Comic-Con attendees.", "Why it matters now: The event is a cultural phenomenon, and Kevin Smith's stand-up shows are a major draw."]	{"heading": "The Story", "body": "San Diego Comic-Con has long been a hub for fans of science fiction, fantasy, and comic books, but this year's event is shaping up to be one of the most exciting yet. With Kevin Smith set to bring his stand-up comedy to the stage, attendees can expect a unique blend of humor and pop culture. As a director and actor, Smith has built a loyal following with cult classics like Clerks and Mallrats, and his stand-up shows are always a hit.\\n\\nBut while fans are busy counting down the days until the convention, parking details have been announced \\u2013 and they're causing headaches. Ace Parking, the company responsible for parking logistics, has revealed the details, but it's unclear how this will impact attendees. With thousands of fa